_examples.ISO_639_3_eng:
A floating-point number with unit and valid range:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_number_float": {
			"_decimals": 2,
			"_unit": "_unit_length_cm",
			"_range_valid": {
				"_min-range-inclusive": 0.0,
				"_max-range-exclusive": 300.0
			}
		}
	}
}
```

A plain string constrained by a regular expression:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string": {
			"_regexp": "^[A-Z]{2,3}$"
		}
	}
}
```

An enumeration value constrained to the ISO 639-3 language vocabulary:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_enum": {
			"_enums": ["ISO_639_3"]
		}
	}
}
```

An unconstrained scalar — any type and value accepted:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {}
}
```

A number with a valid range:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_number": {
			"_range_valid": {
				"_min-range-inclusive": 0,
				"_max-range-exclusive": 100
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `42`, `3.14`, `-100`.

A floating-point weight with two decimal places:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_number_float": {
			"_decimals": 2,
			"_unit": "_unit_weight_kg"
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `3.14159`, `0.0`, `98.6`, `-2.5`.

A non-negative integer count:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_number_integer": {
			"_range_valid": {
				"_min-range-inclusive": 0
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `42`, `-7`, `2024`, `0`.

A string constrained by a regular expression:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string": {
			"_regexp": "^[A-Z]{2,3}$"
		}
	}
}
```

An unconstrained string:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string": {}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `"hello"`, `"IT"`, `"john.doe"`, `"2024-01-15"`.

A date with a lower bound:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string_date": {
			"_range_valid_string": {
				"_min-range-inclusive_string": "1900-01-01"
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `"2024-03-15"`, `"1970-01-01"`, `"2000-12-31"`.

A YMD date field accepting any date from year 2000 onwards:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string_YMD": {
			"_range_valid_string": {
				"_min-range-inclusive_string": "2000"
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `"2024"` (year only), `"202403"` (year-month), `"20240315"` (full date).

A six-character hex colour code:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_string_HEX": {
			"_regexp": "^[0-9A-Fa-f]{6}$"
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `"FF0000"`, `"deadbeef"`, `"0A1B2C3D"`.

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_text": {}
	}
}
```

A stored `_text` value is typically a paragraph or longer narrative — for example, a full definition, a methodology description, or a multi-page report excerpt. Unlike `_string`, it is not suitable for indexing or use as a tag.

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_text_HTML": {}
	}
}
```

Stored value example:

```html
<p>A paragraph with <strong>bold</strong> and <em>italic</em> text.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Item one</li>
  <li>Item two</li>
</ul>
```

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_text_Markdown": {}
	}
}
```

Stored value example:

```
# Title

A paragraph with **bold** and *italic* text.

- Item one
- Item two
```

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_text_SVG": {}
	}
}
```

Stored value example:

```xml
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100" height="100">
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="40" fill="steelblue"/>
</svg>
```

A timestamp accepting only dates from year 2000 onwards (Unix time 946684800):

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_timestamp": {
			"_range_valid": {
				"_min-range-inclusive": 946684800
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `946684800` (2000-01-01T00:00:00Z), `1704067200` (2024-01-01T00:00:00Z).

An enumeration value constrained to ISO 639-3 language codes:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_enum": {
			"_enums": ["ISO_639_3"]
		}
	}
}
```

An unconstrained enumeration value:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_enum": {}
	}
}
```

Stored values (enumeration element `_gid`s): `"ISO_639_3_eng"`, `"ISO_3166_3_ITA"`, `"ISO_4217_EUR"`.

Restricting an `_enum` value to ISO 639-3 or ISO 639-1 language codes:

```json
{
	"_scalar": {
		"_enum": {
			"_enums": ["ISO_639_3", "ISO_639_1"]
		}
	}
}
```

Stored values: `["ISO_639_3"]` (single vocabulary), `["ISO_639_3", "ISO_639_1"]` (two vocabularies), `["ISO_3166_3"]` (country codes only).
